# Copy to `.env.local` for local development. On Vercel, set these in Project Settings → Environment Variables.

# =============================================================================
# Supabase: build (staging) vs production
# =============================================================================
# You maintain TWO Supabase projects:
#   - BUILD = your existing project (local dev, Vercel Preview, Vercel Development)
#   - PROD  = new project for the live site (Vercel Production only)
#
# This app always reads the same variable names; you point them at BUILD or PROD
# per environment. Never commit real keys.

# --- Checklist: new PROD project (do in Supabase Dashboard) ---
# [ ] Create a new Supabase project (region, plan as needed).
# [ ] Settings → API: copy Project URL, anon key, service_role key.
# [ ] Settings → Database: note the database password (for pg_dump / restore).
# [ ] Apply schema: from repo root, after `npx supabase link --project-ref <PROD_REF>` run
#     `npm run supabase:db:push`  OR run SQL files in supabase/migrations in order in SQL Editor.
# [ ] Auth → URL configuration: set Site URL to your production app URL; add Redirect URLs
#     for production (and wildcard paths if you use them, e.g. https://yourdomain.com/**).
#     Include https://yourdomain.com/auth/confirm (email confirmation + OAuth code exchange).
# [ ] Repeat URL configuration on the BUILD project for localhost + Vercel preview URLs.
# [ ] Table editor → documents + storage.objects: confirm Row Level Security is ENABLED and
#     policies match the repo migrations (no permissive “allow all” policies in production).
# [ ] Copy Postgres data from BUILD → PROD (see “Database copy” below) then sync Storage.

# --- Local machine (.env.local) ---
# Usually point at BUILD so you do not touch production data while developing.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_BUILD_PROJECT.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_build_anon_key

# Server-only; required for full Storage checks and any service-role usage. Use BUILD service role locally.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_build_service_role_key

# --- Vercel → Environment Variables (same names, different values per scope) ---
# Production:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL / ANON_KEY / SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY → PROD project
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL → canonical production URL
# Preview + Development:
#   Same three Supabase vars → BUILD project
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL → optional; preview URL is often fine for metadata

# Optional: canonical site URL for metadata (Open Graph, metadataBase). Vercel also sets VERCEL_URL.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.example

# --- One-off: copy Storage bucket `documents` from BUILD to PROD ---
# Do this after DB rows exist in PROD (so file_path values match). Do not commit these to .env.local long-term.
# SOURCE_* = BUILD, TARGET_* = PROD. Use service role keys only in a secure shell.
#   SOURCE_SUPABASE_URL=
#   SOURCE_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#   TARGET_SUPABASE_URL=
#   TARGET_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#   STORAGE_BUCKET=documents
#   DRY_RUN=1
# Then: npm run sync:supabase-storage

# --- OpenAI (server only; never NEXT_PUBLIC_) ---
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Model for chat, summarize, and offertevergelijking (default if unset: gpt-4o-mini).
# For noticeably better reasoning on complex comparisons, set e.g. gpt-4o (higher cost/latency).
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o
# Max completion tokens (hard cap on API output; defaults in code if unset).
# OPENAI_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS=1200
# OPENAI_MAX_COMPARE_OUTPUT_TOKENS=2800
# Project context string length cap for /api/chat (input side).
# OPENAI_PROJECT_CONTEXT_MAX_CHARS=32000
# PDF text per document before compare/summarize (representative fragment if truncated).
# OPENAI_COMPARE_PDF_MAX_CHARS_PER_DOC=24000

# --- Projectuitnodigingen (Resend; server only) ---
# Zonder RESEND_API_KEY en INVITE_EMAIL_FROM wordt geen mail verstuurd; de uitnodigingslink blijft in de API-response voor handmatig kopiëren.
# Maak een API key op https://resend.com — test-afzender: INVITE_EMAIL_FROM=Onboarding <onboarding@resend.dev>
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# INVITE_EMAIL_FROM=Dwellora <uitnodigingen@jouwdomein.nl>

# Supabase Auth (dashboard): Site URL = NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL (or Vercel production URL).
# Redirect URLs: add https://your-domain.example/** and https://YOUR_VERCEL_PROJECT.vercel.app/**
# Include /auth/confirm and /invite/accept paths used after email links.

# =============================================================================
# Database copy (BUILD → PROD) — run from your machine, not from this repo’s CI
# =============================================================================
# Foreign keys to auth.users require migrating auth data together with public schema data.
# Use the connection strings from each project: Settings → Database → Connection string (URI).
# Example flow (adjust for your Postgres tools and Supabase version; test on a backup first):
#
#   pg_dump  --dbname="postgresql://postgres.[BUILD_REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres" \
#            -Fc -f build.dump
#   # Restore into PROD only after PROD schema matches BUILD (migrations applied). May require
#   # excluding owners/extensions per Supabase docs, or using their recommended migration path.
#   pg_restore --dbname="postgresql://postgres.[PROD_REF]:[PASSWORD]@..." --clean --if-exists build.dump
#
# Always read the latest Supabase + Postgres docs before running destructive restore on PROD.

# --- Playwright (CI runs `npm run start`; optional override) ---
# PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000
